   In another development, the Romanian ambassador was summoned to
the Foreign Ministry to hear complaints about ``brutal treatment''
of Polish tourists by Romanian border guards, the state PAP news
agency reported.
   Poland and Romania are Warsaw Pact allies, but relations with
the hard-line communist state have been chilly since Solidarity
took over the Polish government in August.
