<HEAD>With AM-Panama Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates throughout with later info.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a brief summary of events in Panama:
   _U.S. troops attacked Panamanian Defense Forces bases, capturing
or dispersing most PDF troops. U.S. forces appeared to have gained
control but fighting continued.
   _President Bush said in a televised address he ordered American
troops into action ``to protect the lives of American citizens in
Panama and bring Gen. Manuel Antonio Noriega to justice in the
United States.''
   _Noriega was not captured and was in hiding. The United States
$1 million for information leading to his capture.
   _Fifteen American servicemen and one American civilian were
reported killed. One hospital reported at least 52 other people
died.
   _Hostages were reportedly taken from the Marriott Hotel by
Panamanian paramilitary troops. It was unclear how many were
captured and whether all were released.
   _Opposition leader Guillermo Endara was sworn in as president.
The United States recognized his government. The Organization of
American States refused.
   _Most members of Congress in both parties supported the action.
   _The Soviet Union condemned the attack as a violation of
international law.
