   Stock prices drifted lower today, registering no
strong reaction to the U.S. military action in Panama.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 10.67 to
2,684.94 by 3 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Losers outnumbered gainers by about 9 to 8 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 690 up, 779 down and
